narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: If you are in Naval ROTC and you don't want to discover halfway through that you aren't actually enrolled in your Navy classes, for the love of Jesus, Mary and Joseph, sign up for this class. This happened to one of the freshmen this year and his life was pretty rough for about two weeks. Make sure your shoes are shined and that you don't look like trash, or else risk the wrath of SSgt Long.
Understandably a necessary course/lab for ROTC students. Beyond any midshipmen, I wouldn't recommend this course to anyone.
marching, drilling, physical fitness tests, and guest speakers. E CINERE PROELIUM.
Summary: A section of time where NROTC students do whatever the unit needs them to do. Presentations, paperwork, fitness tests, meet with guests, etc.
